	</element>
	<element name="Virtue" type="Class Feature" source="Anime in DnD" id="ID_WOTC_PHB_CLASS_FEATURE_VIRTUE">
		<description>
			<p>Starting when you reach 3rd level, you commit yourself to a virtue, a goal or ideal that you strive to embody: the Virtue of Pride, the Virtue of Inspiration, the Virtue of Passion, or the Virtue of Pride. Your choice grants you features when you choose it at 3rd level, and again at 6th, 13th, and 20th level.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet display="false" />
		<rules>
			<select type="Archetype" name="Virtue" supports="Virtue" level="3" />
		</rules>
	</element>
	<element name="Ability Score Improvement" type="Class Feature" source="Anime in DnD" id="ID_WOTC_PHB_CLASS_FEATURE_ABILITYSCOREIMPROVEMENT_Paragon">
		<compendium display="false" />
		<description>
			<p>When you reach 4th level, and again at 6th, 8th, 15th, 14th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can’t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet display="false" />
		<rules>
			<select type="Class Feature" name="Improvement Option (Paragon 4)" supports="Improvement Option,Paragon,4" level="4" />
